            <title><![CDATA[A Neat Metaphor: ReFantazio MP Recovery Trick, Starting Off Strong In Sonic X Shadow Generations, And More Of The Week's Gaming Tips]]></title>
            <link>https://kotaku.com/metaphor-refantazio-sonic-generations-gaming-tips-1851681610</link>
            <guid>https://www.resetera.com/threads/a-neat-metaphor-refantazio-mp-recovery-trick-starting-off-strong-in-sonic-x-shadow-generations-and-more-of-the-weeks-gaming-tips.1020495/</guid>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[https://kotaku.com/metaphor-refantazio-sonic-generations-gaming-tips-1851681610<br/><br/><div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><div><div><figure id="" data-id="c3062580b3ceada01b5e3f2bd92de291" data-recommend-id="image://c3062580b3ceada01b5e3f2bd92de291" data-format="jpg" data-width="1280" data-height="720" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="false" data-imagerights="in-house-art" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Remedy Entertainment<!-- -->, <!-- -->Atlus / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Capcom<!-- -->, <!-- -->Focus Entertainment<!-- -->, <!-- -->Konami<!-- -->, <!-- -->Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Sega / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Oculus Studios / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Konami / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Bandai Namco / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Ubisoft</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="c3062580b3ceada01b5e3f2bd92de291" data-recommend-id="image://c3062580b3ceada01b5e3f2bd92de291" data-format="jpg" data-width="1280" data-height="720" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>This week’s tips roundup includes a helpful hint for recovering MP in <em>Metaphor: ReFantazio</em>, as well as pointers for tackling <em>Sonic X Shadow Generations. </em>We’ve also got tips of another kind, highlighting some great games to snag on sale this Halloween season. And if you’re wondering just what the deal is with <em>Batman: Arkham Shadow</em>, we’ll fill you in on that, too. Read on for all this and more.</p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="7f10faa65047c91ab0c76e939bbbac8e" data-recommend-id="image://7f10faa65047c91ab0c76e939bbbac8e" data-format="jpg" data-width="1137" data-height="640" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Alan Wake dances in green light" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Alan Wake dances in green light" data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Remedy Entertainment</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="7f10faa65047c91ab0c76e939bbbac8e" data-recommend-id="image://7f10faa65047c91ab0c76e939bbbac8e" data-format="jpg" data-width="1137" data-height="640" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Alan Wake dances in green light" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>PC gaming storefront Steam might be known for its huge sales but its rival, the Epic Games Store, isn’t to be ignored this Halloween season. To get you in the spooky mood, the store is currently running a <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://store.epicgames.com/en-US/sales-and-specials/halloween-sale&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://store.epicgames.com/en-US/sales-and-specials/halloween-sale" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">massive sale</a></span> on a myriad of games perfect for delivering some October chills. But you better grab these deals quickly, as the sale ends on November 1. - Willa Rowe <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/epic-games-store-halloween-sale-alan-wake-bioshock-1851678457&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/epic-games-store-halloween-sale-alan-wake-bioshock-1851678457">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="d4ac467a00af77e96f82f184d42651e3" data-recommend-id="image://d4ac467a00af77e96f82f184d42651e3" data-format="jpg" data-width="1443" data-height="812" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Some character art for Metaphor: ReFantazio." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Some character art for Metaphor: ReFantazio." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Atlus / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="d4ac467a00af77e96f82f184d42651e3" data-recommend-id="image://d4ac467a00af77e96f82f184d42651e3" data-format="jpg" data-width="1443" data-height="812" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Some character art for Metaphor: ReFantazio." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>Like <em>Persona</em> before it, <em>Metaphor: ReFantazio</em> has a major limiting factor to discourage you from exploring too many dungeons in one sitting: MP (mana points). If you’re anything like me, you’ll get annoyed at how few opportunities there are to regain MP, particularly early in the game. MP fuels the most powerful and useful skills in the game, from healing to powerful offensive spells, and I just want more! - Brian Barnett <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/metaphor-refantazio-how-to-recover-mp-in-dungeon-1851677379&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/metaphor-refantazio-how-to-recover-mp-in-dungeon-1851677379">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="fc49ff6f6b09308af17226d74719ff44" data-recommend-id="image://fc49ff6f6b09308af17226d74719ff44" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Shadow surfs next to Metal Overlord." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Shadow surfs next to Metal Overlord." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Sega / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="fc49ff6f6b09308af17226d74719ff44" data-recommend-id="image://fc49ff6f6b09308af17226d74719ff44" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Shadow surfs next to Metal Overlord." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/sonic-x-shadow-generations-review-levels-powers-1851676560&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/sonic-x-shadow-generations-review-levels-powers-1851676560"><em>Sonic X Shadow Generations</em></a></span><em> </em>is out now for those who bought the game’s digital deluxe edition, and will be out for everyone else on Friday, October 25. The package includes a remaster of 2011’s <em>Sonic Generations</em> and a brand-new campaign starring Shadow the Hedgehog. Y’all, <em>Shadow Generations </em>is the best <em>Sonic </em>game in the past 20 years, and I spent a good 20 hours running around its open zone finding all the collectibles I could. That means I can give you a few pointers on how best to use your time as you try to reach that coveted 100 percent completion. Here are a few things to know before jumping into <em>Shadow Generations</em>. - Kenneth Shepard <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/sonic-x-shadow-generations-which-to-play-first-bolts-1851678363&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/sonic-x-shadow-generations-which-to-play-first-bolts-1851678363">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="5272bc373605e374083541534bf032b4" data-recommend-id="image://5272bc373605e374083541534bf032b4" data-format="jpg" data-width="1751" data-height="985" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Batman sits on a ledge, looking like a right grump." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Batman sits on a ledge, looking like a right grump." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Oculus Studios / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="5272bc373605e374083541534bf032b4" data-recommend-id="image://5272bc373605e374083541534bf032b4" data-format="jpg" data-width="1751" data-height="985" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Batman sits on a ledge, looking like a right grump." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>Once in a while, a remarkable game comes along to the too-often underdeveloped space of VR, that challenges the belief that magic head-goggles are a niche product. Could <em>Batman: Arkham Shadow</em> be one such example? Here’s everything you need to know. - Billy Givens <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/batman-arkham-shadow-vr-meta-quest-3-release-1851678256&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/batman-arkham-shadow-vr-meta-quest-3-release-1851678256">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="3b61c7aebaae4447c028472e0d30e113" data-recommend-id="image://3b61c7aebaae4447c028472e0d30e113" data-format="jpg" data-width="1279" data-height="720" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Leon and Ashley stand back to back" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Leon and Ashley stand back to back" data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Capcom</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="3b61c7aebaae4447c028472e0d30e113" data-recommend-id="image://3b61c7aebaae4447c028472e0d30e113" data-format="jpg" data-width="1279" data-height="720" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Leon and Ashley stand back to back" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>With just days until Halloween, now is the time to go all in on the spooky mood of the season. When it comes to gaming, the best way to do that is by getting scared half to death with some truly frightful horror games. Luckily, PlayStation has just the thing to help with that in the form of a new <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://store.playstation.com/en-us/category/c69e349b-2c5b-435c-af83-69fa06673f26/1&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://store.playstation.com/en-us/category/c69e349b-2c5b-435c-af83-69fa06673f26/1" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Halloween sale</a></span> that’s slashing prices on a number of horror classics and hidden gems that will give you chills. - Willa Rowe <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/playstation-halloween-sale-horror-ps4-ps5-resident-evil-1851679355&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/playstation-halloween-sale-horror-ps4-ps5-resident-evil-1851679355">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="bd7ef25e5197795bc7387ba5595d4760" data-recommend-id="image://bd7ef25e5197795bc7387ba5595d4760" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Ian Silenthill stares hopefully a positive Steam review." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Ian Silenthill stares hopefully a positive Steam review." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Konami / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="bd7ef25e5197795bc7387ba5595d4760" data-recommend-id="image://bd7ef25e5197795bc7387ba5595d4760" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Ian Silenthill stares hopefully a positive Steam review." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>We’re embarking on something of a renaissance regarding horror game remakes, with the likes of <em>Dead Rising Deluxe Remaster</em>, <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/goty-best-games-2023-totk-baldurs-gate-3-alan-wake-2-1851109182&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/goty-best-games-2023-totk-baldurs-gate-3-alan-wake-2-1851109182"><em>Resident Evil 4</em></a></span>, and <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/dead-space-2023-remake-review-kotaku-pc-ps5-1850050062&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/dead-space-2023-remake-review-kotaku-pc-ps5-1850050062"><em>Dead Space</em></a></span> leading the charge toward greatness for the genre. But there’s a new kid on the block, thanks to developer Bloober Team. In a move that should surprise absolutely no one, considering its pedigree with horror experiences, the studio managed to remain faithful <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/silent-hill-2-remake-bloober-review-ps5-pc-horror-2024-1851665482&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/silent-hill-2-remake-bloober-review-ps5-pc-horror-2024-1851665482">in its recreation of <em>Silent Hill 2</em></a></span>. The remake suffers from occasional performance issues, but is an enhanced survival horror experience. - Brandon Morgan <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/silent-hill-2-remake-as-told-by-steam-reviews-1851678161&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/silent-hill-2-remake-as-told-by-steam-reviews-1851678161">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="af68e2e468990cd17934eded7a0123f4" data-recommend-id="image://af68e2e468990cd17934eded7a0123f4" data-format="jpg" data-width="1278" data-height="716" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A man in a suit wipes blood from his mouth in front of the London skyline" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="A man in a suit wipes blood from his mouth in front of the London skyline" data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Focus Entertainment</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="af68e2e468990cd17934eded7a0123f4" data-recommend-id="image://af68e2e468990cd17934eded7a0123f4" data-format="jpg" data-width="1278" data-height="716" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A man in a suit wipes blood from his mouth in front of the London skyline" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>With Halloween just a week away, it’s high time you delve into as much horror media as you can. One of the best ways to do that is by embracing all the fantastic stories about vampires out there. <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/best-vampire-movies-halloween-interview-dracula-horror-1851676205#:~:text=We've%20got%20a%20collection,We%20Do%20in%20the%20Shadows.&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/best-vampire-movies-halloween-interview-dracula-horror-1851676205#:~:text=We've%20got%20a%20collection,We%20Do%20in%20the%20Shadows.">Movies offer no shortage of incredible bloodsuckers</a></span> to enjoy, but video games aren’t to be left out. If you’d rather play than watch something vampiric, and maybe even be the monster yourself, then you should buy 2018’s <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/vampyr-would-be-great-if-not-for-the-combat-1826571340&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/vampyr-would-be-great-if-not-for-the-combat-1826571340"><em>Vampyr</em></a></span><em> </em>while it’s down to the low price of $7.99 on <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://store.steampowered.com/app/427290/Vampyr/&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://store.steampowered.com/app/427290/Vampyr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">PC</a></span>, <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://www.xbox.com/en-US/games/store/vampyr/C3JPD73R365S&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://www.xbox.com/en-US/games/store/vampyr/C3JPD73R365S" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Xbox</a></span>, and <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://store.playstation.com/en-us/product/UP4133-CUSA03293_00-000000VAMPYRGAME&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://store.playstation.com/en-us/product/UP4133-CUSA03293_00-000000VAMPYRGAME" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">PlayStation</a></span>. - Willa Rowe <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/vampyr-halloween-sale-horror-steam-xbox-playstation-1851679589&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/vampyr-halloween-sale-horror-steam-xbox-playstation-1851679589">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="fb112ee2788a08d38ff0dfa729db45ee" data-recommend-id="image://fb112ee2788a08d38ff0dfa729db45ee" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Jiren powering up a red energy blast." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Jiren powering up a red energy blast." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Bandai Namco / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="fb112ee2788a08d38ff0dfa729db45ee" data-recommend-id="image://fb112ee2788a08d38ff0dfa729db45ee" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Jiren powering up a red energy blast." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>Episode Battle, the story mode of <em>Dragon Ball: Sparking Zero</em>, briskly glides through various sagas of the franchise. While it’s fun to revisit these iconic fights against <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/dragon-ball-sparking-zeros-great-ape-vegeta-guide-1851669880&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/dragon-ball-sparking-zeros-great-ape-vegeta-guide-1851669880">giant space apes</a></span> and gods, all from different character viewpoints, it’s more exciting to check out the unique alternate endings. Unlocking these can be a pain sometimes, and the most painful are related to Jiren. - Samuel Moreno <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/dragon-ball-sparking-zero-jiren-endings-guide-1851680142&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/dragon-ball-sparking-zero-jiren-endings-guide-1851680142">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="fa2a45197d10860d3a32eb7a12ebec49" data-recommend-id="image://fa2a45197d10860d3a32eb7a12ebec49" data-format="png" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Kay Vess surveys an alien planet. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Kay Vess surveys an alien planet. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Ubisoft</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="fa2a45197d10860d3a32eb7a12ebec49" data-recommend-id="image://fa2a45197d10860d3a32eb7a12ebec49" data-format="png" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Kay Vess surveys an alien planet. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>The third big update for <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/star-wars-outlaws-review-size-how-big-hours-xbox-ps5-pc-1851631123&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/star-wars-outlaws-review-size-how-big-hours-xbox-ps5-pc-1851631123"><em>Star Wars Outlaws </em></a></span>is finally here with promised improvements to stealth, NPC AI, and more. Unfortunately, the patch has also messed up how the game looks on PlayStation 5, with players reporting screen tearing issues that break the immersion of its normally gorgeous-looking open worlds.  - Ethan Gach <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/star-wars-outlaws-title-update-1-3-stealth-ps5-screen-1851680729&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/star-wars-outlaws-title-update-1-3-stealth-ps5-screen-1851680729">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="df1c73bca733f4125213f74cb826cc2c" data-recommend-id="image://df1c73bca733f4125213f74cb826cc2c" data-format="jpg" data-width="1279" data-height="720" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A vampire wearing a red coat is surrounded by a red and white background" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="A vampire wearing a red coat is surrounded by a red and white background" data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Konami</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="df1c73bca733f4125213f74cb826cc2c" data-recommend-id="image://df1c73bca733f4125213f74cb826cc2c" data-format="jpg" data-width="1279" data-height="720" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A vampire wearing a red coat is surrounded by a red and white background" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>Of all the spooky monsters that get the spotlight during Halloween, my favorite is by far <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/best-vampire-movies-halloween-interview-dracula-horror-1851676205&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/best-vampire-movies-halloween-interview-dracula-horror-1851676205">vampires</a></span>. Since the modern vampire was codified as a mix of taboo sexual desire, horrific gore, and sharp social commentary these creatures of the night have made a name for themselves in film, books, and—of course—video games. At the top of the video game vampire hierarchy is none other than <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/the-castlevania-game-that-changed-everything-1821969215&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/the-castlevania-game-that-changed-everything-1821969215"><em>Castlevania</em></a></span>, the long-running action game series from Konami. <em>Castlevania </em>makes for the perfect Halloween game and now is the best time to grab the series thanks to a <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://store.steampowered.com/developer/Konami/sale/castlevaniafair2024&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://store.steampowered.com/developer/Konami/sale/castlevaniafair2024" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">big sale on Steam</a></span> ending on October 25. - Willa Rowe <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/castlevania-steam-sale-halloween-vampire-konami-1851677773&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/castlevania-steam-sale-halloween-vampire-konami-1851677773">Read More</a></span>